# Pull requests — two-phase story workflow (GitHub-aligned)

## When this applies

Use when the user wants a **pull request** tied to `docs/agile/epics/**/stories/US-*-*/STORY.md`, especially when they ask for a **draft**, **review first**, or **approve then publish**.

## Phase 1 — Draft only (no GitHub, or GitHub Draft)

1. Resolve the story folder: `node scripts/pr-story.mjs resolve US-DOMAIN-NNN` (prints path).
2. Build the PR body (from user paste, from `STORY.md` / `TASKS.md`, or edits to existing `PR_BODY.md`).
3. Write **`PR_BODY.draft.md`** in that story folder (same folder as `STORY.md`).
4. Show the user the draft path and a short summary (title + first lines). **Stop and wait** for explicit approval — do **not** open a non-draft PR without consent.

**Optional GitHub Draft (good for CI + early feedback):** After local body is approved, prefer:

```bash
node scripts/pr-story.mjs create US-DOMAIN-NNN --title "[US-…] …" --draft
```

Uses `PR_BODY.draft.md` by default (`--body-file` to override).

## Phase 2 — After user approval

Interpret the user’s intent:

| User says (examples) | Action |
|---------------------|--------|
| Approve **draft on GitHub** / “open draft PR” | `node scripts/pr-story.mjs create … --draft` (push branch first if needed). |
| Approve **ready for review** / “publish PR” / “ready for reviewers” | If PR already exists as draft: `node scripts/pr-story.mjs promote <N>`. If not created yet: `node scripts/pr-story.mjs create … --ready` (creates non-draft PR). |
| Copy draft to canonical body only | `node scripts/pr-story.mjs init-draft` copies `PR_BODY.md` → `PR_BODY.draft.md` only when seeding from published template; to promote draft text to `PR_BODY.md`, copy file explicitly or use `save-draft` source = edited draft. |

## Title convention

```text
[US-{DOMAIN}-{NNN}] {short title}
```

## GitHub practices (follow these)

- Prefer **`gh pr create --draft`** first so the PR does not imply “ready to merge” and reviewers get a clear signal ([GitHub: draft PRs](https://docs.github.com/en/pull-requests/collaborating-with-pull-requests/proposing-changes-to-your-work-with-pull-requests/about-pull-requests#draft-pull-requests)).
- Use **`gh pr ready <N>`** to move draft → ready for review when the user approves.
- Keep the body in-repo: **`PR_BODY.md`** (published) vs **`PR_BODY.draft.md`** (work in progress). Either may be committed; teams may gitignore `*.draft.md` if preferred.
- One story per branch when possible (`docs/agile/GIT_STRATEGY.md`).
- Do not add `Made-with: Cursor` trailers (`.cursor/rules/commit-messages.mdc`).
- After merge: update `STORY.md`, `EPIC.md`, `TEAM_STATUS.md` (`docs/agile/HOW_TO_USE.md` §7).

## Script reference

```text
node scripts/pr-story.mjs resolve US-DESIGN-002
node scripts/pr-story.mjs init-draft US-DESIGN-002
node scripts/pr-story.mjs save-draft US-DESIGN-002 path/to/body.md
node scripts/pr-story.mjs create US-DESIGN-002 --title "[US-DESIGN-002] …" --draft
node scripts/pr-story.mjs create US-DESIGN-002 --title "[US-DESIGN-002] …" --ready
node scripts/pr-story.mjs promote 42
```

Full guide: `docs/agile/guides/STORY_PR_WORKFLOW.md`
